Looks like it's having trouble loading the library when creating the browser widget. I'm not sure why it's happening but here are some guesses:

- You have an older version of the SWT .so on your path
- Downloaded wrong version (e.g. for windows instead of linux)
- Incomplete download

Try checking these and if it still doesn't work, SWT team can help debug.

This is a known bug with IBM jre cxia32142-20050929.  If you use a newer 1.4.2 jre or a 1.5 jre then this will work for you.


*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of bug 139519 ***
